      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROMAN CHARLIE (1) has been racing well, filling a top-five position at his last five starts including a second most recently at Geelong over 2100m. Has the benefit of a good draw. Won't find this any harder and he can add to the impressive recent record. KEAYANG ALABAMA (8) went back last start then worked home in good style with a long sustained effort to finish 2.5 metres from the winner in second at Kilmore over 1690m, adding to his second at Terang two runs back. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. Good enough to put himself back in the winners' stall. LUVN MARY (3) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 1750m at Birchip. Should run a big race. BUBBLE OVER (4) is in the mix following a fourth at her most recent appearance over 2195m at this track.",
